In relation to the Nigeria Oil Prospecting Licence (Opl) 245 trial, Eni welcomes today’s judgment of full acquittal of all charges, since there was no case, by the Court of Milan.  According to the management of Eni, after almost three years of trial, the judgment by the Court has finally established that the company, the CEO Claudio Descalzi and the management involved in the proceedings have all behaved in a lawful and correct manner.  The statement further stated that Eni has throughout maintained its full confidence in the Court’s fair and balanced investigation.  Today, in the statement sent to The AmehNews noted that Eni expresses its gratitude for the trust placed by its stakeholders throughout the course of the trial, particularly in upholding the company’s management and the conduct of its business, and respecting its reputation